    <title>Provide code</title>
    
    <p>
    <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> has a version control system at SourceForge.net.
    You can clone the repository with the following command:
    </p>
    
    <p>
    <cmd>hg clone http://hg.code.sf.net/p/modem-manager-gui/code modem-manager-gui-code</cmd>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Note, this clone command doesn't give you write access to the repository.
    </p>
    
    <p>
    For general help on how SourceForge works, see the
    <link href="https://sourceforge.net/p/forge/documentation/ToC/">SourceForge documentation</link>.
    </p>
    
    <p>
    <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> source code is stored inside Mercurial repository, so
    you don't have to read Git tutorials; just make sure you know basic Mercurial commands
    and able to work on SourceForge platform.
    </p>
    
